# This file exists so `ui/wasm/dist/` is checked in as an empty
# directory. The server crate uses `include_dir!("…/wasm/dist")` which
# panics at compile time if the path is missing, and we don't want
# every contributor (or every cargo build) to need trunk installed up
# front. Trunk overwrites everything else in this directory.
#
# Real build flow:
#   1. `trunk build --release` populates this directory with
#      `index.html`, the wasm-bindgen JS loader and the .wasm blob.
#   2. `cargo build --release -p botwork-ui-server` embeds the
#      populated directory via `include_dir!`.
#
# If `cargo build` runs before `trunk build` the server binary still
# compiles but only `/healthz` works. The integration test asserts a
# marker string from a real index.html and emits an IGNORED line when
# the marker is missing, so this failure mode is loud in CI (which
# always runs trunk first) and silent locally for contributors who
# don't need the UI loop.
